<inglise> Whereas, pursuant to the Treaty, all discriminatory treatment based on nationality with regard to establishment and to the provision of services is prohibited from the end of the transitional period; whereas the principle of such national treatment applies in particular to the right to join professional organizations where the professional activities of the person concerned necessarily involve the exercise of this right; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: asutamislepingu kohaselt on alates &uuml;leminekuperioodi l&otilde;pust asutamise ja teenuste osutamise puhul keelatud igasugune diskrimineerimine kodakondsuse p&otilde;hjal; seda v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;tet kohaldatakse eelk&otilde;ige &otilde;iguse suhtes &uuml;hineda kutseorganisatsioonidega, kui selline &otilde;igus kaasneb automaatselt asjaomase isiku ametialase tegevusega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas not all Member States impose conditions for the taking up and pursuit of activities of insurance agent and broker; whereas in some cases there is freedom to take up and pursue such activities but in other cases there are strict provisions making access to the profession conditional upon possession of formal evidence of qualifications; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;ik liikmesriigid ei s&auml;testa tingimusi kindlustusagendi v&otilde;i kindlustusmaakleri t&ouml;&ouml; alustamise ja j&auml;tkamise kohta; m&otilde;ningatel juhtudel on olemas vabadus alustada ja j&auml;tkata seda tegevust, kuid m&otilde;ningatel juhtudel on ette n&auml;htud ranged tingimused, mille kohaselt sellel erialal tegutsemise tingimuseks on ametlikud kvalifikatsioonit&otilde;endid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in view of the differences between Member States as regards the scope of activities of insurance agent and broker, it is desirable to define as clearly as possible the activities to which this Directive is to apply; </inglise>
<eesti> pidades silmas liikmesriikidevahelisi erinevusi kindlustusagentide ja kindlustusmaaklerite tegevuse ulatuses, on soovitav v&otilde;imalikult t&auml;pselt m&auml;&auml;ratleda tegevused, mille suhtes k&auml;esolevat direktiivi kohaldatakse; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, moreover, Article 57 of the Treaty provides that, in order to make it easier for persons to take up and pursue activities as self-employed persons, Directives are to be issued for the mutual recognition of diplomas, certificates and other evidence of formal qualifications and for the coordination of the provisions laid down by law, regulation or administrative action in Member States; </inglise>
<eesti> lisaks sellele on asutamislepingu artiklis 57 s&auml;testatud, et lihtsustamaks inimestel f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjaks hakkamist ja sellise isikuna tegutsemist, tuleb v&auml;lja anda direktiivid diplomite, tunnistuste ja muude ametlike kvalifikatsioonit&otilde;endite vastastikuse tunnustamise ja liikmesriikides &otilde;igusnormidega etten&auml;htud s&auml;tete koosk&otilde;lastamise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in the absence of mutual recognition of diplomas or of immediate coordination, it nevertheless appears desirable to facilitate the effective exercise of freedom of establishment and freedom to provide services for the activities in question, in particular by the adoption of transitional measures of the kind envisaged in the General Programmes (3) in order to avoid undue constraint on the nationals of Member States in which the taking up of such activities is not subject to any conditions; </inglise>
<eesti> diplomite vastastikuse tunnustamise v&otilde;i viivitamatu koosk&otilde;lastamise puudumise korral on siiski soovitav aidata kaasa asutamisvabaduse ja teenuste osutamise vabaduse tulemuslikule kasutamisele k&otilde;nealustes tegevusvaldkondades eelk&otilde;ige sellega, et v&otilde;etakse vastu samalaadsed &uuml;leminekumeetmed, nagu on kavandatud &uuml;ldprogrammides, (3) v&auml;ltimaks p&otilde;hjendamatuid piiranguid isikutele, kes on p&auml;rit liikmesriikidest, kus selliste tegevuste alustamise suhtes ei kehti mingeid eeltingimusi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to prevent such difficulties arising, the object of the transitional measures should be to allow, as sufficient qualification for taking up the activities in question in host Member States which have rules governing the taking up of such activities, the fact that the activity has been pursued in the Member State whence the foreign national comes for a reasonable and sufficiently recent period of time, in cases where previous training is not required, to ensure that the person concerned possesses professional knowledge equivalent to that required of the host Member State's own nationals; </inglise>
<eesti> v&auml;listamaks selliste raskuste tekkimist, peaks &uuml;leminekumeetmete eesm&auml;rgiks olema see, et vastuv&otilde;tvas liikmesriigis, kus sellise tegevuse alustamise suhtes kehtivad teatavad eeskirjad, v&otilde;iks juhtudel, kui ei n&otilde;uta varasemat koolitust, k&auml;sitleda piisava kvalifikatsioonina k&otilde;nealuste tegevuste alustamiseks asjaolu, et sellise tegevusega on liikmesriigis, kust v&auml;lisriigi kodanik p&auml;rit on, tegeletud m&otilde;istliku ja suhteliselt hiljutise aja jooksul, ja tagada sellega, et asjaomase isiku erialased teadmised on samav&auml;&auml;rsed teadmistega, mida n&otilde;utakse vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi enda kodanikelt; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in view of the situation in the Netherlands, where insurance brokers are, depending on their professional knowledge, divided up into several categories, an equivalent system should be provided for in respect of nationals of other Member States who wish to take up an activity in one or other of the categories concerned; whereas the most appropriate and objective criterion for this purpose is the number of employees whom the person concerned has or has had working under him; </inglise>
<eesti> pidades silmas olukorda Madalmaades, kus kindlustusmaaklerid on erialaste teadmiste p&otilde;hjal jagatud mitmesse kategooriasse, tuleks samalaadne s&uuml;steem kehtestada ka teiste liikmesriikide kodanike suhtes, kes soovivad hakata tegutsema &uuml;he v&otilde;i teise asjaomase kategooria raames; selle k&otilde;ige otstarbekam ja objektiivsem kriteerium on t&ouml;&ouml;tajate arv, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tavad v&otilde;i on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud asjaomase isiku alluvuses; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, where the activity of agent includes the exercise of a permanent authority from one or more insurance undertakings empowering the beneficiary, in respect of certain or all transactions falling within the normal scope of the business of the undertaking or undertakings concerned, to enter in the name of such undertaking or undertakings into commitments binding upon it or them, the person concerned must be able to take up the activity of broker in the host Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> kui kindlustusagendi t&ouml;&ouml; hulka kuulub &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitme kindlustusseltsi antud alaliste volituste kasutamine, millega ta v&otilde;ib asjaomase kindlustusseltsi v&otilde;i asjaomaste kindlustusseltside tavalise &auml;ritegevuse raames aset leidvate teatavate v&otilde;i k&otilde;igi toimingute puhul v&otilde;tta endale sellise kindlustusseltsi v&otilde;i selliste kindlustusseltside nimel nende jaoks siduvaid kohustusi, v&otilde;ib k&otilde;nealune isik hakata vastuv&otilde;tvas liikmesriigis tegutsema maaklerina; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the purpose of this Directive will disappear once the coordination of conditions for the taking up and pursuit of the activities in question and the mutual recognition of diplomas, certificates and other formal qualifications have been achieved; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolev direktiiv kaotab otstarbe p&auml;rast seda, kui on saavutatud k&otilde;nealuste toimingute alustamise ja j&auml;tkamise tingimuste koosk&otilde;lastamine ning diplomite, tunnistuste ja muude ametlike kvalifikatsioonit&otilde;endite vastastikune tunnustamine; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in so far as in Member States the taking up or pursuit of the activities referred to in this Directive is also dependent in the case of paid employees on the possession of professional knowledge and ability, this Directive should also apply to this category of persons in order to remove an obstacle to the free movement of workers and thereby to supplement the measures adopted in Council Regulation (EEC) No 1612/68 of 15 October 1968 on freedom of movement for workers within the Community (1), as amended by Regulation (EEC) No 312/76 (2); </inglise>
